page.title: 03Ecology.
page.content: In Maidencombe and surrounding district there are lots of plants and animals.There are lots of holes belonging to rabbits,foxes and badgers.There are many wild flowers including red campion,arum lily, buttercup,dandelion,valerium,wild violets,groundsel,celandine,cow parsley and poppies.A family of house sparrows were nesting in the old court house.Other birds seen were blackbirds ,blue tits,kestrels and black headed gull.There is a Judas tree growing in the grounds of the Court House Hotel. The animals and plants are all healthy because there is no pollution to spoil the plants or the area.The footpaths are well cared for and the hedges grow wild.The beaches are clean and not spoilt by man.
